# CVE-2026-40973: Spring Boot Arbitrary Code Execution and Session Hijacking
# Severity: HIGH
# Reason: Spring Boot 3.4.5 contains this vulnerability. Upgrade to 3.5.14+ fixes it, but
#         Spring Cloud 2024.0.1 (used by services) only supports Spring Boot 3.4.x.
#         Upgrading Spring Cloud to 2025.0.0 (pending release) would allow Spring Boot 3.5.x upgrade.
#         This is a known limitation of current Spring Cloud release train.
# Mitigation: Plan upgrade to Spring Cloud 2025.0.0 in next maintenance window.
# Review Date: 2026-06-01
CVE-2026-40973
